                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.11L5232/522: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-21T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 21, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. On February 4 Department transmitted to German Embassy a note urging that the
                    German Government expedite the presentation to the Mixed Claims Commission of
                    such evidence as the German Government intends to present in regard to the
                    sabotage claims pending before the Commission.</p>
                <p>The German Ambassador advises that this note was transmitted to his
                    Government.</p>
                <p>Please endeavor promptly to find an opportunity to press for an early disposition
                    of this matter laying particular stress upon the fact that the delay is unduly
                    augmenting the expenses of the Commission; that it cannot be attributed to any
                    lack of attention to these cases on the part of the American Agency; and that it
                    would seem to be equally to the interests of both Governments that the work of
                    the Commission be promptly brought to a close.</p>
                <p>Please keep Department informed of developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
